snippet: Mr. Page, who was scrutinized by the F.B.I. on suspicion of private communications with senior Russian officials last summer, said he would meet with “business leaders and thought leaders.”...
abstract: Carter Page, former foreign policy adviser for Pres-elect Donald J Trump who was scrutinized by the Federal Bureau of Investigation on suspicion of private communications with senior Russian officials, travels to Moscow; disputes rumors that he is conduit between Trump and Russian government.
lead_paragraph: Mr. Page, who was scrutinized by the F.B.I. on suspicion of private communications with senior Russian officials last summer, said he would meet with “business leaders and thought leaders.”

headline.main: Carter Page, Ex-Trump Adviser With Russian Ties, Visits Moscow
headline.print_headline: Ex-Adviser to Trump Makes Visit to Moscow
